Date: Sat, 29 Aug 1998 08:05:43 -0600
From: Hal Nash <hnash@wyoming.com>

Your question, "can one remove tonsils twice?," can be answered with a
"yes." My pharyngeal tonsils (a.k.a. adenoids) grew back and were removed a
second time. I was a young child, so this is evidence that tonsillar
material may regrow.
--
Hal Nash
e-mail: hnash@wyoming.com
[Nice to see one's rhetorical question answered, twice. From Hal's comment,
they clearly grow back quickly. Not something that the average veterinarian
would have much experience with. Thanks. - Mod.MHJ
